### Fix #7 — Added Statistical Significance Testing

**Problem identified:**
The central claim of the project ("the Hybrid model is better than BM25") was supported only by a point estimate difference in mean errors (3.87 → 3.83, a difference of 0.04 ranking positions). A mean difference without variance estimates or significance testing is scientifically inadmissible. On a sample of ~414 queries, a Δ = 0.04 could easily be noise.

**Fix applied:**
A **Wilcoxon signed-rank test** (non-parametric, paired) is applied in Notebook 5 between the per-query error vectors of BM25 and the Hybrid model, for both Level 1 and Level 2. The Wilcoxon test is appropriate here because:
1. It makes no normality assumption (ranking errors are heavily right-skewed).
2. It is paired (the same set of queries is evaluated by both models).
3. It is robust to small sample sizes.

A p-value < 0.05 is required to claim statistically significant improvement.

